The paper deals with unsupervised action detection in videos, which is a problem in computer vision. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also uses unsupervised learning techniques, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.MM (Multimedia). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of pre-processing techniques for generating video highlights, which could fall under cs.IR (Information Retrieval) or cs.CL (Computation and Language).
